         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">21/10/90. ¶  ¶ I have examined and compared your  ¶ Sterculia ¶  No. 1129 carefully, dear Mr Holtze, and recognised it as  ¶ new ¶ ; I have called it  ¶ S. holtzei. ¶  The manuscript with the descript...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">90.10.21b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Maurice Holtze</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">GRG 19/391, State Records of South Australia, Adelaide.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">21/10/90.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ihre Sterculia 1129 habe ich sorgfältig untersucht u. verglichen, lieber Herr Holtze, u als </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">neu</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> erkannt, u solche S. Holtzei genannt. Das Manuscript der Beschreibung ist bereits an die Königl. Gesellschaft von Sydney gesandt. Es wäre gut, besonders bei der engen Verwandtschaft dieser Art mit mehreren indischen Arten, dass </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">reife Frucht</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> herbei geschafft würde! Dies ohnehin erleichtert in </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">allen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Fällen die Bearbeitung von Pflanzen aller Arten. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ihr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Wenn die Früchte kommen, werde ich solche auch beschreiben. Samen von dieser Neuheit wären auch erwünscht.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Auf der Rinde dieser Sterculia fand ich </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">zwei</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Flechten (Lichen-) Arten, die </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">eine</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> ganz kleine schwarze Tüpfel bildend, die </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">andere</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> kleine runde Früchte tragend mit eingebogenem Rande. Ihr Sohn mit seinen jungen Augen würde wohl </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">mehr</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Lichenen dort entdecken, nachdem nun seine Aufmerksamkeit darauf gerichtet ist.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">21/10/90.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have examined and compared your <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Sterculia</seg> No. 1129 carefully, dear Mr Holtze, and recognised it as <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">new</hi>
               </seg>; I have called it <seg style="font-style: italic; ">S. holtzei.</seg> The manuscript with the description has already been sent to the Royal Society of Sydney.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See B91.13.02, p. 175.</p>
               </note> It would be well, especially considering the close relationship of this species with several Indian species, if <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ripe fruit</hi>
               </seg> could be procured!<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">In M to M. Holtze, 8 February 1891, M acknowledged receiving young fruit of the species and asked for ripe fruit if possible.</p>
               </note> Moreover this makes the work on plants of all species easier in <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">all</hi>
               </seg> cases.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">When the fruits arrive, I shall describe them as well. Seeds of this novelty would be desirable, too.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On the bark of this <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Sterculia</seg> I found <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">two</hi>
               </seg> lichen species, the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
               </seg> forming tiny black dots, the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">other</hi>
               </seg> bearing small round fruiting bodies with an incurved edge. Your son<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Nicholas Holtze.</p>
               </note> with his young eyes would probably be able to discover <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">more</hi>
               </seg> lichens there, now that his attention has been drawn to them.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <name key="Sterculia%20holtzei">Sterculia holtzei</name>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
